.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/implementation-summary.md:51:| **Repository default** | Unchanged; compiled routing remains default-off |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/implementation-summary.md:60:The decision packet settles the ruling on the analysis: adopt a staged path to compiled routing as the effective default rather than flipping the default now. No runtime work has begun. The current live integration remains additive metadata only, the compiled and legacy decisions remain identical, and the repository flag remains off by default. The operator may override the ruling to flip-now at any time; that override is available but not blocking.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/implementation-summary.md:76:Add re-mint-required CI for stale manifests, then enable compiled routing in one named environment profile while the repository default remains off.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/implementation-summary.md:80:Derive both eligibility consumers from the manifest-freshness rule already owned by `decision-record.md`, then stage the global default one hub at a time while preserving `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING=0` as the fleet-wide kill-switch.
