.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/implementation-summary.md:27:| **Frozen scorer state** | Pinned and untouched by this documentation phase |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/implementation-summary.md:48:No Lane C runtime file, fixture, report renderer, manifest, routing input, or frozen scorer file was modified by this planning phase.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/implementation-summary.md:67:| Exercise the public front door in a child process | Tests the real flag and serving gates and prevents parent environment leakage. |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/implementation-summary.md:70:| Use shared status and eligibility interfaces | Prevents Lane C from inventing a local hub list or alternate drift meaning. |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/implementation-summary.md:99:4. **This phase covers deterministic Mode A only.** It does not add paid real-model verification or network activity.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/implementation-summary.md:108:- [ ] Finalize P3 eligibility and manifest discovery without a hardcoded hub map.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/plan.md:17:- Match phases to the stated scope; remove setup theater that does not change the outcome.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/plan.md:52:- [ ] P0 provides a stable public compiled front door and machine-readable serving-status cause.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/plan.md:53:- [ ] P3 provides shared eligibility and manifest discovery without a local hub list.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/plan.md:118:- Enumerate legacy telemetry and compiled target shapes for all seven hub archetypes.
