.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/references/common-pitfalls.md:3:description: Deep-dive on recurring feature-catalog defects with worked before/after fixes, plus the template-versus-reference split for the catalog package.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/references/common-pitfalls.md:5:  - "feature catalog pitfalls"
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/references/common-pitfalls.md:6:  - "feature catalog common mistakes"
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/references/common-pitfalls.md:7:  - "feature catalog roadmap drift"
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/references/common-pitfalls.md:8:  - "feature catalog source anchors"
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/references/common-pitfalls.md:23:A feature catalog fails quietly. Structure validation passes, links resolve, and the package still misleads readers — because the failures are about *content trust*, not markup. The pitfalls below are the ones that erode that trust. Each entry states the symptom, why it breaks reader trust, and the concrete fix.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/references/common-pitfalls.md:29:### Treating the catalog like a roadmap
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/references/common-pitfalls.md:33:**Why it breaks**: A catalog's one job is to answer "what does the system do today?" The moment a reader finds one aspirational claim, every claim becomes suspect.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/references/common-pitfalls.md:41:**Why it breaks**: Playbooks, READMEs, and specs link to catalog paths. A rename silently breaks every inbound link, and CI catches it only if those links live in checked markdown.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/references/common-pitfalls.md:53:### Execution-heavy scenario detail in the catalog
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/references/common-pitfalls.md:55:**Symptom**: A catalog entry grows step-by-step "do X, observe Y" validation scenarios.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/references/common-pitfalls.md:57:**Why it breaks**: That is a manual testing playbook's job. Mixing it in blurs the boundary and bloats the inventory the catalog is supposed to keep scannable.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/references/common-pitfalls.md:59:**Fix**: Keep execution matrices in the playbook. In the catalog, describe *what* the behavior is and link to the playbook for *how to validate it*. See the catalog/playbook boundary in `SKILL.md`.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/references/common-pitfalls.md:61:### Playbook cross-references drifting from catalog names
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/references/common-pitfalls.md:63:**Symptom**: A feature is renamed or re-scoped in the catalog, but the playbook that links to it still uses the old name.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/references/common-pitfalls.md:67:**Fix**: When a feature name changes, update the catalog entry and every playbook link in the same change. The two documents are a pair; edit them together.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/references/common-pitfalls.md:81:**Why it breaks**: The skill advisor harvests doc triggers from that frontmatter (memory deliberately does not index skill docs), so a file with no triggers is invisible to routing.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/references/common-pitfalls.md:83:**Fix**: Add at least three phrases, leading with the exact H3 heading used in the root catalog, then natural-language alternates and the tool or command name:
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/references/common-pitfalls.md:87:  - "memory indexing"          # matches the root-catalog H3
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/references/common-pitfalls.md:88:  - "index a saved memory"     # natural-language alternate
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/references/common-pitfalls.md:98:- Use the **templates** in `../assets/feature-catalog/` to scaffold the actual files — the empty root-catalog and per-feature shapes, their frontmatter blocks, and their publishing checklists.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/references/common-pitfalls.md:108:- [examples.md](examples.md) - a live catalog that avoids these pitfalls
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/references/common-pitfalls.md:109:- [../assets/feature-catalog/feature-catalog-snippet-template.md](../assets/feature-catalog/feature-catalog-snippet-template.md) - per-feature scaffold with its own authoring notes
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/references/common-pitfalls.md:110:- [create-manual-testing-playbook references](../../create-manual-testing-playbook/references/README.md) - the playbook side of the catalog/playbook boundary
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/SKILL.md:2:name: create-feature-catalog
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/SKILL.md:3:description: Create sk-doc feature-catalog packages with a root catalog, category folders, per-feature files, and auditable source anchors.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/SKILL.md:8:<!-- Keywords: create-feature-catalog, feature catalog, feature inventory, catalog package, per-feature files, source anchors, root catalog, capability inventory, /create:feature-catalog -->
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/SKILL.md:12:`create-feature-catalog` is the feature-inventory workflow packet of the `sk-doc` parent hub. It authors canonical current-state catalogs rooted at `feature-catalog/feature-catalog.md`, with category folders and one per-feature reference file per root catalog entry.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/SKILL.md:14:Feature catalogs are the canonical inventory for what a system does today. They organize capabilities by category, summarize current behavior in a root catalog, and link to per-feature files that carry implementation anchors, tests, and metadata.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/SKILL.md:16:Core principle: use the root catalog for stable inventory and navigation, and use per-feature files for implementation truth and traceable source anchors.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/SKILL.md:18:This packet owns `/create:feature-catalog`, its `references/` set (indexed by `references/README.md`), and `assets/`. It consumes shared sk-doc validation and writing standards from `../shared/`.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/SKILL.md:29:- Splitting a large feature surface into a root catalog plus per-feature files.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/SKILL.md:31:- Creating or updating `feature-catalog/feature-catalog.md`.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/SKILL.md:36:Keyword triggers: `feature catalog`, `feature inventory`, `catalog package`, `per-feature files`, `source anchors`, `root catalog`, `capability inventory`, `capabilities`, `/create:feature-catalog`.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/SKILL.md:46:- The requested catalog would describe planned behavior rather than current shipped behavior.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/SKILL.md:47:- The task is only document quality review of an existing catalog. Use `create-quality-control`.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/SKILL.md:55:Create a feature catalog when the system needs a canonical capability inventory.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/SKILL.md:68:- The product is too volatile for a maintained catalog to stay accurate.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/SKILL.md:74:  YES -> Create a feature catalog package
