.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/SKILL.md:203:The source assets keep the filenames `feature-catalog-template.md` and `feature-catalog-snippet-template.md` until their separate source-file migration. Those filenames are authoring inputs, not emitted package names.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/SKILL.md:211:1. Read the target system docs, source files, command surfaces, MCP tool lists, tests, and existing README material before drafting the catalog.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/SKILL.md:212:2. Decide whether a catalog is warranted; use a README summary instead when the feature surface is small, complete, stable, or too volatile for a maintained catalog.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/SKILL.md:215:5. Create `feature-catalog/feature-catalog.md` from `assets/feature-catalog-template.md`.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/SKILL.md:216:6. Create one category folder per root section using a descriptive kebab-case slug such as `category-name`; the root catalog listing defines display order.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/SKILL.md:217:7. Create one per-feature file for each root entry using `assets/feature-catalog-snippet-template.md`.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/SKILL.md:223:13. Validate the root catalog and each per-feature leaf file with shared validation (see §7).
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/SKILL.md:236:The root catalog is the top-level inventory and navigation layer.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/SKILL.md:254:Package highlights for root catalogs:
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/SKILL.md:262:Do not overload the root catalog with:
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/SKILL.md:276:Each per-feature file is the detailed reference entry for one catalog item.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/SKILL.md:288:- At least three trigger phrases matching the H3 heading in the root catalog.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/SKILL.md:313:Feature catalogs and manual testing playbooks serve different purposes.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/SKILL.md:317:| Feature catalog | What does the system do today? |
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/SKILL.md:318:| Manual testing playbook | How do we validate that behavior manually? |
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/SKILL.md:322:- Playbooks should link back to the matching catalog entry when one exists.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/SKILL.md:324:- Manual execution scenario matrices belong in playbooks, not catalogs.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/SKILL.md:326:Validation workflow — run from the repo root so the validator resolves the `feature_catalog` doc type on per-feature leaves (leaf detection accepts the canonical `feature-catalog/<category>/` path during the bounded compatibility window):
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/SKILL.md:330:# canonical feature-catalog package, never an ancestor with shipped legacy roots.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/SKILL.md:331:python3 .opencode/skills/sk-doc/shared/scripts/check_no_hyphenated_catalog_content.py <new-content-staging-root>
