    11	
    12	# Context-First Intake And Visible Plan
    13	
    14	<!-- sk-doc-template: skill_asset_feature_catalog -->
    15	
    16	## 1. OVERVIEW
    17	
    18	The `sk-design` hub gathers enough context to avoid generic design output before routing or transport work.
    19	
    20	The intake captures goal, surface, inputs, constraints, and proof expectations. When a missing fact would change routing or acceptance, the hub asks one focused question; otherwise it proceeds with a stated assumption.
    21	
    22	---
    23	
    24	## 2. HOW IT WORKS
    25	
    26	The hub reads `mode-registry.json` and resolves the smallest useful mode: `interface`, `foundations`, `motion`, `audit`, or `md-generator`. Generic "make it look good" prompts default to `interface`; explicit static-system, temporal, audit, or extraction language routes to the matching mode.
    27	
    28	Before substantial design direction, build-ready guidance, implementation handoff, or transport work, the hub shows a concise plan naming the selected mode or bundle, loaded or missing context, intended design moves or audit dimensions, proof required before ready, and any handoff target.
    29	
    30	---
    31	
    32	## 3. SOURCE FILES
